{
  "stem": "18470.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I can remember as a child the processions, the church processions going up and down [NON-ENGLISH], because they would emanate at the top of the street.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They'd pass our house.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And sometimes people would stop in, and wanted something to eat or use the facilities.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it was a very easy relationship for a long time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I can remember that, except on one-- one day a year when the whole town turned topsy turvy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was on [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was the holiday which commemorated the canonization of Werner, who was [SIGHS] murdered in the 14th century by his nursemaid, as it turned out, but not before the Jews of Oberwesel had been accused of his death and his ritual murder.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "His blood was to have been used to bake matzahs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And if there's anything more reprehensible to imagine, I can't imagine it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because Jews have a natural aversion to blood.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But that was the libel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a blood libel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Werner apparently swam upstream from Bacharach, which was the next town, to Oberwesel, the downstream town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He swam upstream in the Rhine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He swam upstream and pointed the finger to the synagogue in Oberwesel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's-- that was the legend as to how they knew that the Jews of Oberwesel were the murderers of Werner.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a pogrom, which has been widely documented.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Catholic church made a Saint of Werner then.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And each year, his-- his day would be commemorated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's the day my friends, whom I played with most of the year, would beat me up and accuse me of having killed Werner, and the association therefore also, again, of Jew as the Christ killer.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
